<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>I think that fallacy should be called the anthropic fallacy (I don't think the fallacy has a name yet).<p>The anthropic principle is that even though the number of planets hospitable to life is tiny the probability that humanity evolved on a planet that is hospitable to human life is 100%. The examples you gave are symmetrical.</font></span><p><font size=1><font color=#f6f6ef>-----</font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=120></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3392701 href="vote?for=3392701&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%6f%4c%72%32%61%65%43%68%42%37"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3392701></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=zackattack">zackattack</a> 39 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3392701">link</a></span></div><br>
